    "Together with the director of the Berlin Museum, <a href=\"/bodew\">Wilhelm Bode</a>, he was the author of eight volumes on Rembrandt paintings, which appeared between 1897 and 1904 (1905?).": [],
    "In 1906, the year of the Rembrandt Commemoration, he edited <em>Die Urkunden \u00fcber Rembrandt</em>, and the first catalog of Rembrandt drawings.": [],
    "In the same year he was awarded, together with four other Rembrandt scholars (<a href=\"/bodew\">Wilhelm Bode</a>, <a href=\"/brediusa\">Abraham Bredius</a>, <a href=\"/vethj\">Jan Veth</a>, and <a href=\"/michele1828\">\u00c9mile Michel</a>), a doctorate <em>honoris causa</em> at the University of Amsterdam.": [],
    "His most important work appeared between 1907 and 1928 in ten volumes: <em>Beschreibendes und kritisches Verzeichnis der Werke der hervorragendsten holl\u00e4ndischen Maler des XVII.": [
